rComments: This professor was unable to explain most of the concepts, if you really want to understand Managerial Accounting, be prepared to learn the material all by yourself. Also, if you have any issues in this course (technical/health related), this professor will throw you under the bus...SHE DOESN'T CARE, you are just a number.
She clearly cares about her students and empathizes with our situation. She really spends the time to go through content in detail and emphasizes what we need to focus on to maximize our marks.
This professor is confusing and can not teach. Will need to teach yourself everything good luck and avoid if possible.

Shes very kind! On the other hand, her way of explaining is complex at times and she goes on tangents. The practice problems she offered were not enough for chapter 10-11-11A-12. Everything was rushed at the end of the year for those chapters. She wants you to succeed! She is there to answer questions. Very quick to respond! Would take again :)

This is the kindest prof. She is very clear of her expectations and grading. There are two lectures per week where the first one is recorded and the second one is where solutions are given for handouts (not recorded). This motivated me to attend her lectures. Reuses examples from handouts and assignments in midterms and exams so attend the class!
Horrible prof that can't teach anything. You're going to have to teach yourself everything from the textbook. Avoid if you can.

She's a really nice prof and cares a lot about her students. During class discussions, she made every student's answer feel valid which made it more comfortable and welcoming to speak without the fear of being "wrong". Also very responsive to emails. I found her lectures interesting and well-structured so I'm surprised at all of the low reviews.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Really nice lady but bad prof. She goes on tangents at the beginning of class and then goes 20 minutes over class time---lectures not recorded. As well, I find shes not able to explain a lot of the concepts, and the lecture notes also fail to make the concepts comprehensible. A prof perhaps with too much knowledge and doesnt know how to teach?

If you cannot find good profs to teach accounting, then don't open too many accounting courses that claim to help you get a CPA, but they won't in reality. The course requires a huge amount of practice to do well, and the prof does nothing to help you understand the materials since she can't explain them. Prepare yourself for the worst. Good luck.
One of the most disappointing profs at Telfer. Avoid if possible.

The worst prof I've ever had at Telfer. Her class is boring and you have to spend time trying to learn from the textbook. needs improvement

An amazing professor for this course, and cares very dearly for her students. She is clear on what's expected on quizzes & exams, teaches via blackboard examples, receptive to feedback, & keeps the class engaged. Textbook is helpful for practise problems but it's not necessary to read. To do well, do all practise problems and don't miss class!
One of my favorite professors at U of Ottawa
Pro. Li is a nice person. Just follow her guide and do the assigned exercises. Her in-class illustrations are similar to mid-term and final exams, so don't miss the lectures.

Second half of course kills you just like Financial does; so start going to DGDs and doing the assigned (optional)  homework problems after the midterm if you want to stand a chance on the final. Good prof, very accommodating to questions and if you come late to one of the 3 quizzes. Does exam type questions every now and then so definitely show up

+She is there for you. Visited her outside office hours, stayed even after class to ask her to repeat what she said in class. +Examples in class similar to midterm and final +Easy A  -Her accent is tough

This was one of my favourite courses I've taken thus far with Telfer and Dr. Li was a big part of that. She tells you exactly what to expect on assessments and she does a terrific job teaching the subject matter. As well, you can tell she really cares about her students. I didn't find the textbook very helpful, aside from doing practise problems.

She's a nice lady, but she's an absolutely terrible lecturer. On the bright side, her midterm and quizzes are fair, other than that, she has very limited English (hard to understand), spends 90% of the lecture running through exercises without explaining how she got there, you'll leave her class wondering what the hell happened in there.

Due to her limited English skill, you really need to be open minded to understand what she says. Always stay until the the end of the class, n never skip! The stuff she explains in class 95% same w tests (Easy A).  She is super helpful and willing to stay until like 10.20 pm to explain stuffs to you and lots of extra office hours.
One of those classes where you will actually have to read the book; she's not that bad but you'll have to put in a LOT of personal  effort to get a good grade!
don't ever take this class, i bet 100% you will regret. worst accounting prof~! so boring and not helpful at all.

She is difficult to understand when speaking or writing, but the tests given in the class cover the topics she showed in class. Study hard for the quiz's because they can lower your grade if you neglect them. You need to show up for every class to understand since cost accounting is difficult.
